			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName> <date>Sep 5&#44; 1855</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">During my<lb/> absence from here <persName>Dr. Eckman</persName> paid<lb/> me for the Occident&#59; please acknow&#45;<lb/>&#45;ledge the same.  Your Books shipped<lb/> pr. ship &#8220;Snap Dragon&#8221; have not arrived yet.  If they were<lb/> here now&#44; I could readily dispose of<lb/> them&#44; being near our Holidays.<lb/>  My principal object to write you with<lb/> this mail is to inform you of an organization<lb/> of a charitable society that is in the act of<lb/> being formed by our Jewish Ladies in this<lb/> city.  A Number of Ladies <del>assembled</del><lb/> met for the first time at <persName>Mr. Jacob<lb/> Rich&#39;s</persName> House &#38; organized the society&#44;<lb/> of which <persName>Mrs. Abm. Tandler</persName> acted the<lb/> President &#38; <persName>Mrs. Rich</persName> secretary.  A<lb/> subsequent meeting was then called in<lb/> the synagogue of the Congregation of Emanu&#45;<lb/>&#45;El on <date><sic>sunday</sic> the 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of <sic>aug.</sic></date> when a<lb/> large numer of Ladies were present.  The object<lb/> &#38; importance of the Benefit</p>
		
